Kino is the protagonist of the novella. Kino is a dignified, hardworking, impoverished native who works as a pearl diver. He is a simple man who lives in a brush house with his wife, Juana, and their infant son, Coyotito, both of whom he loves very much. After Kino finds a great pearl, he becomes increasingly ambitious and desperate in his mission to break free of the oppression of his colonial society. Ultimately, Kinoâ€™s material ambition drives him to a state of animalistic violence, and his life is reduced to a basic fight for survival.Read anin-depth analysis of Kino.